Adapted files (derived from ARS code):
  uncited_assertions.py        <- scripts/uncited_assertion_detector.py +
                                  scripts/_claim_audit_constants.py (the D4-c
                                  detector and its constants, merged into one
                                  module). Behavioral changes relative to
                                  upstream: the citation condition is
                                  retargeted from markdown <!--ref:slug-->
                                  markers to LaTeX markers (\cite-family
                                  commands, \ref{tab:/fig:}, textual
                                  "Table N"/"Figure N" own-result references);
                                  the trigger vocabulary is extended
                                  (outperform-family verbs, "improved by"
                                  phrases, p-values); a hyphenated-identifier
                                  guard (CIFAR-10, GPT-4) and extra section
                                  cues (equation, algorithm, theorem, ...)
                                  are added; a LaTeX prose view plus the
                                  check_tex / uncited_assertion_check entry
                                  points and report writer are new.

Original files (this repository, but NC applies to the directory as a unit):
  __init__.py, _latex.py, _files.py, citation_context.py
  (citation_context.py is an original, simpler LaTeX descendant of the
   failure classes exercised by ARS's
   scripts/check_v3_7_3_three_layer_citation.py; no ARS code is reused.)

NOTE: because this directory is CC BY-NC 4.0, the Research-Agent-Harness
project as distributed includes non-commercial-only components. Commercial
use of the combined work is not permitted; remove this directory for a
pure-MIT build.
